nodes.title: CFG & STEPS INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
This workflow uses higher than normal CFG.
So 6.0 is normal.
If you want lower then bypass the "AdaptiveProjectedGuidance" node first.

20-26 steps is a good average.
Higher rank of flash-heun lora r01-r128 allows lower steps but at some cost to realism/detail/coherency.

nodes.title: ADVANCED NOISE INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
Noise types can be changed for various image types.
Experiment with it.
wavelet seems good for realism.
gaussian is most common noise type.
Connect SIMPLE NOISE node to the reroute to the right of this node for ComfyUI default.

nodes.title: STARTING NOISE INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
0.9 is good for most photorealism.
1.0 is default by ComfyUI.
0.91-0.99 is good for some detailed artwork.

nodes.title: COMPLEX COMPENSATE INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
Lower value for more complex images.
0.6 for very simple images.

nodes.title: SAMPLER INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
er_sde is optimal for medium to lower step count.
heun or dpmpp_sde can also be used but use at half normal step count.
euler or deis for high step count.
